<beginCreatedObjects>
<beginStartingNarrative>
In this game, you will learn how to draw the correct conclusions regarding: 
- sample size evaluation, 
- interpretation of the significance of the coefficient of determination, 
- outlier identification and removal, and 
- Mean Magnitude of Relative Error (MMRE) significance.
In addition, in this game, you must demonstrate your ability to correctly interpret the statistical results. 
You will have access to an Excel file containing the database of completed software projects, their characteristics, and the full steps of building each of the linear regression models. 
Your challenge is to evaluate the statistical results for 10 different scenarios, and to answer four questions related with the statistical performance of the model. 
In terms of strategy, we recommend making full use of the Excel file to: 
- understand steps of building up a regression model, 
- understand statistical thresholds for all the criteria, 
- practicing interpretation rather than calculation, 
- developing critical judgment about the performance of statistical models.

Good Luck.

Excel file link : 

https://etsmtl365-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/g/personal/sion-israel_sion_1_ens_etsmtl_ca/EX-XSSjLBnBGhPUv-fcKYJQBG2jr7GO01ykjx7TbpleBBQ?e=iKc85u
<endStartingNarrative>
